th and emerging markets  strategic acquisition and divestiture  governance and operations  brands and partnerships  worldwide partnership with christian h cooper  current initiatives  higher education  medicine  architecture and design  wiley online library  corporate culture  apple controversy  kirtsaeng v john wiley  sons  references  bibliography  external links historyedit the hoboken new jersey headquarters wiley was established in  when charles wiley opened a print shop in manhattan the company was the publisher of such th century american literary figures as james fenimore cooper washington irving herman melville and edgar allan poe as well as of legal religious and other nonfiction titles wiley later shifted its focus to scientific technical and engineering subject areas abandoning its literary interests charles wileys son john born in flatbush new york  october  died in east orange new jersey  february  took over the business when his father died in  the firm was successively named wiley lane  co then wiley  putnam and then john wiley the company acquired its present name in  when johns second son william h wiley joined his brother charles in the business through the th century the company expanded its publishing activities the sciences and higher education since the establishment of the nobel prize in  wiley and its acquired companies have published the works of more than  nobel laureates in every category in which the prize is awarded one of the worlds oldest independent publishing companies wiley marked its bicentennial in  with a yearlong celebration hosting festivities that spanned four continents and ten countries and included such highlights as ringing the closing bell at the new york stock exchange on may  in conjunction with the anniversary the company published knowledge for generations wiley and the global publishing industry  depicting wileys pivotal role in the evolution of publishing against a social cultural and economic backdrop wiley has also created an online community called wiley living history offering excerpts from knowledge for generations and a forum for visitors and wiley employees to post their comments and anecdotes highgrowth and emerging marketsedit wiley in december  opened an office in dubai to build on its business in the middle east more effectively the company has had an office in beijing china since  and china is now its sixthlargest market for stem content wiley established publishing operations in india in  though it has had a sales presence since  and has established a presence in north africa through sales contracts with academic institutions in tunisia libya and egypt on april   the company announced the establishment of wiley brasil editora ltda in são paulo brazil effective may   strategic acquisition and divestitureedit wileys scientific technical and medical business was significantly expanded by the acquisition of blackwell publishing in february  the combined business named scientific technical medical and scholarly also known as wileyblackwell publishes in print and online  scholarly peerreviewed journals and an extensive collection of books major reference works databases and laboratory manuals in the life and physical sciences medicine and allied health engineering the humanities and the social sciences through a backfile initiative completed in   million pages of journal content have been made available online a collection dating back to  wileyblackwell also publishes on behalf of about  professional and scholarly societies among them are the american cancer society acs for which it publishes cancer the flagship acs journal the sigma theta tau international honor society of nursing and the american anthropological association other major journals published include angewandte chemie advanced materials hepatology international finance and liver transplantation launched commercially in  wiley interscience provided online access to wiley journals major reference works and 