ooks and subscription products scientific technical medical and scholarly… morejohn wiley  sons inc nyse jwa is a global publisher of print and electronic products providing content and solutions to customers worldwide the companys core businesses produce professional and consumer books and subscription products scientific technical medical and scholarly journals encyclopedias books and online products and textbooks and educational materials the john wiley  sons has previously acquired a number of companies including inscape holdings and efficient learning systems john wiley  sons it department is responsible for the oversight of all data security across the enterprise and for enterprise information security resources and planning for the company technology for the company is overseen by a chief technology officer  the company will places a focus on increase in expanding and enhancing its mobility environment for its presence in the ereader and ebook market the systems development group is responsible for telecommunications and network services for corporate locations the group also maintains the technical services functions for desktop computers and is responsible for server support function hosted on a unix platform teams are also responsible for the development implementation and support of the companys corporate applications the enterprise technology services ets group handle the database administration and related systems functions at the company the company has several it directors who oversees responsibilities like global business intelligence solutions  hris systems publishing technology network services wan performance application service and database technology john wiley has a history of outsourcing its it needs including a longstanding relationship with provider mindtree which manages wileys information technology needs in bangalore india and in australia mindtree manages portions of infrastructure operations business intelligence and support for a variety of business systems john wiley  sons incs organizationwide data volume is approximately  tb –  pb and is growing at an annual rate of   its data environment consists of highly fragmented data that is primarily deployed on premises in a purposebuilt appliance  the company uses relational database to store data primarily sourced from enterprise applications john wiley  sons inc uses a nas environment to back up its file data it uses native snapshot and replication as its main backup application its daily and weekly total data backup is tb and tb respectively the it budget is typically finalized in q it intelligence snippets  john wiley  sons inc describes data replication times as its biggest storage headache its top storage pain points are wan being too slow compliance issues and the lack of modernizingvirtualizing solutions for systems and tape that are no longer viable john wiley  sons inc is hoping to deploy total data transformation in the near future  the company is currently investing heavily in storage servers and development costs solutions john wiley  sons inc was looking to deploy mobile application solutions over the subsequent  months it also is planning to deploy cloud based services for applications and infrastructure during this time frame but has no plans for new cloud platforms the priority is on using cloud services for email collaboration and conferencing with the benefit of being able to free up additional it resources for inhouse projects and systems ones that need to stay in house sources at john wiley  sons inc indicate the companys file transfers and data replication solutions cause the most strain on its network environment senior sources at john wiley  sons indicate that perimeter security mobile access and intersite communication will be priorities for its security efforts over the coming  months over the next  month the company is looking to deploy private cloud storage  • tb –  pb data volume companywide across  to  data centers and ex